<br>
<br>
In Eternal Darkness, I finished Chapter 5: The Lurking Horror. The game, I admit, has startled me several times so far with enemies attacking suddenly, recently with a huge glass window shattering loudly, and new demons often violently tearing their way out dead enemies.<br>
<br>
And at times, it generally is quite creepy/scary with the plot itself slowly progressing throughout each chapter, as well as whispering voices in the background, weird spell chanting, insanity effects, the occasional corpses and blood, etc. The general atmosphere is great, and especially effective if you're playing it in the dark.<br>
<br>
But the gameplay is fun as well... lots of puzzle stuff and item use that reminds me of a simpler Shadowgate (though you generally aren't killed for mistakes) and fighting is pretty standard, but becomes more complex when you learn spells to enchant weapons and such. You can also target specific body parts of an enemy. Decapitate them so they can't see. Or hack off their arms so they can't attack you anymore. <br>
<br>
I'd guess I'm still a little less than halfway through the game with about 5 hours of play. Unless things get worse or something, I'd say it's been worth the money. Apparently short length is the only problem, but I seem to remember hearing of a new difficulty that opens up.<br>
